cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the problem of link prediction in social networks. It also involves the use of multiple aligned social networks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SOC (Social and Economics Networks). The paper proposes a network embedding framework, which could be related to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of graph attention mechanism could also be related to the sub-category of cs.SD (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves the prediction of links, which could be related to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
